title: For Sale:  NIB CZ P10c These are one nice gun, VERY hard to find and only have 1
postcontent: Many years in the making, they're pleased to announce the latest addition to the CZ line of handguns - the P-10 C. Much more than just their take on the striker-fired pistol, the P-10 is decidedly CZ, from the way it feels to the way it shoots.First order of business, ergonomics. Anyone who's picked up a CZ 75 for the first time gets it - it just has to feel right in the hand. With the CZ grip angle, the P-10 avoids that 'brick-in-the-hand' feeling that has plagued many in the striker-fired genre, allowing it to point naturally. A mild palm swell, deep beavertail, and three interchangeable backstraps make the P-10 fit a wide variety of hands as if it were built for them. Because it was.Next up, trigger. So many striker-fired pistols do many things right, falling short when it comes time to pull the trigger. Designed to minimize creep and stacking, the P-10's trigger breaks at a clean 4-4.5lbs and rebounds with a short, positive reset, meaning single shots can be meticulously placed while follow-ups are effortless.Built to withstand the rigors of military use, its fiber-reinforced polymer frame and hardy nitride finish are made for the daily grind. A generous trigger guard allows use with gloved hands while being undercut to allow as high a grip as possible, and a set of metal tactical 3-dot sights allow for one-handed manipulation of the slide on a belt.Like all CZ pistols, the P-10 is built with their legendary cold hammer forged barrel. The 'C' in the name indicates that it is compact in both frame and slide size, and magazines are of the same family as the hammer-fired P-07, meaning the P-10 C holds 15+1 in 9mm in a flush-fitting mag. Take-down of the P-10 will be familiar to most fans of striker-fired guns, and even more pleasing will be holster compatibility with some of the most common guns on the market.Type: PistolAction: Single/DoubleCaliber: 9mm LugerBarrel Length: 4"Capacity: 15+1Safety: Trigger/Firing PinGrips: Black Interchangeable BackstrapSight Configuration: 3-DotWeight: 26 ozFrame Finish: Black NitrideFrame Material: PolymerBarrel Type: Cold Hammer-ForgedSlide Description: Black Nitride***No trades at this time*******Background included in price of gun****

The ejector rod is probably a replacement, screw heads are not engraved and the ejector rod is not numbered. It was very common for ejector rod housings to be removed on revolvers used in battle. title: For Sale:  Remington 700 is a SCAM
postcontent: Beware of Remington 700 BDL with Bushnell scope.  This is a SCAM.  Please flag it!  Just copy and paste the description of the firearm into a Google search and you'll find that gun for sale on the first site that pops up.  Please flag that post!Remember:  ALWAYS deal FTF.  (Face to Face).  NEVER send money/check to private party.   Things to look for here on Armslist.  Scammers often don't use specific location, for instance they will say "Washington, Washington" as the location.  Usually they aren't registered with Armslist but if they are usually it is a very recent (same day most likely) that they registered the account.  My account here says:  "Registered on 4/5/2013" which shows my account has been open for 4 years so is much less likely to be a scam.  The scam accounts are almost always unregistered or like I said were just very recently registered.  Hope that helps guys.  I know most of you probably already were aware of the things I mentioned above.  Not looking to get into major discussions or anything just trying to help out my fellow armslisters.  Have a great Friday and weekend.  Molon LabeTHANK YOU TO THOSE WHO FLAGGED THE DUMBASS
